<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-14-0794 </DOCNO><TEXT>Any future agreement between the superpowers regarding standing arsenalsof intercontinental ballistic missiles will undoubtedly feature dramaticreductions in their numbers. Recent history suggests that the surplusmissiles must be destroyed in order to provide a secure and mutuallyverifiable means of ensuring compliance. But demolition of the STARTinventories in turn denies their utility as a valuable scientific resource.In keeping with the spirit of START, this paper suggests that the demandsof mutual verification and peaceful civilian needs can be reconciledby jointly and cooperatively using the idled ICBM launchers to exploitthe scientific and commercial promises of space. 12 refs., 4 figs.</TEXT></DOC>